content: Gravatar - Globally Recognized Avatars WordPress.com Create a free website. VaultPress Backup and security scanning for your site. Akismet The anti-spam service for the web. Crowdsignal Create surveys for the web and mobile. G Menu What is Gravatar? How to Use Gravatar Help WordPress.com Sign In Gravatar.com A Globally Recognized Avatar Your Gravatar is an image that follows you from site to site appearing beside your name when you do things like comment or post on a blog. Avatars help identify your posts on blogs and web forums, so why not on any site? Matt embarcadero and townsend, sf ca In 2002 I started contributing to Open Source software, and life has just gotten better from there. Co-founder of WordPress, founder Automattic. View Complete Profile Introducing Gravatar ► JavaScript required to play Introducing Gravatar. For Site Owners Setting up Gravatars on your site is easy; you don't even need an account! Plugins are available for leading blog software and content management systems, and our tutorials will have you running Gravatars in no time.Example Plugins and Code → Millions of avatar images are being served over 8.6 billion times per day. Join some of the other sites that use Gravatar: Gravatar Users Blog Developer Resources Technical Support An Automattic Team Languages Privacy Policy
